    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{{\frac{z}{\left(z-3\right)^{2}}}}{{\frac{3z}{z^{2}-9}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{z+3}{3\mathopen{}\left(z-3\right)}, z\ne 0\hbox{ and }z\ne -3</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simply the complex fraction <m>\frac{{\frac{z}{\left(z-3\right)^{2}}}}{{\frac{3z}{z^{2}-9}}}</m>, we multiple the numerator and denominator with the common denominator of <m>{\frac{z}{\left(z-3\right)^{2}}}</m> and <m>{\frac{3z}{z^{2}-9}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
  \frac{{\frac{z}{\left(z-3\right)^{2}}}}{{\frac{3z}{z^{2}-9}}} \amp = \frac{{\frac{z}{\left(z-3\right)^{2}}}}{{\frac{3z}{\left(z+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(z-3\right)}}} \\
  \amp = \frac{{\frac{z}{\left(z-3\right)^{2}}\mathopen{}\left(z+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(z-3\right)^{2}}}{{\frac{3z}{\left(z+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(z-3\right)}\mathopen{}\left(z+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(z-3\right)^{2}}} \\
  \amp = \frac{{z\mathopen{}\left(z+3\right)}}{{3z\mathopen{}\left(z-3\right)}},z\ne-3 \\
  \amp ={\frac{z+3}{3\mathopen{}\left(z-3\right)}, z\ne 0\hbox{ and }z\ne -3}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>z</m> and <m>z+3</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>{z \ne -3\hbox{ and }z \ne 0\hbox{ and }z \ne 3}</m>.</p>
</solution>
